name: New Caledonia
summary: Political turmoil unfolds in New Caledonia, a French Pacific territory, with the imposition of an emergency following fatal unrest. A police shooting claimed the life of a man, fueling ongoing tensions. The independence party has declined a dialogue with a French delegation. Amidst the unrest, graduates from the College of New Caledonia celebrated their future. Despite the turmoil, France has rushed to enable New Caledonian participation in European elections, facing indifference from the majority. The protests have further strained relations with France, with some expressing distrust. Missionaries have been relocated due to the unrest.

name: iOS 18 beta
summary: Apple's iOS 18 beta is now available for download, offering a glimpse into upcoming features and enhancements for iPhones. The beta release includes significant changes such as a customizable lock screen, new messaging capabilities, and improved privacy measures. To install the beta, users can enroll in the Apple Developer Program or use public beta channels. Notable additions in iOS 18 include a new "Focus" mode for managing notifications, a redesigned Weather app, and an enhanced Photos app with improved search capabilities. The beta also introduces Apple Intelligence features such as "Live Text" and "Visual Look Up," extending these features to additional content types and languages. However, some users have noted that the iOS 18 beta lacks certain anticipated features, such as the rumored "Apple Intelligence" update. Nonetheless, the beta provides an early opportunity to experience the latest software from Apple and provide feedback on its development.

name: Dragon Boat Festival
summary: Dragon boat festivals have taken place or are scheduled to take place across Ontario. Notably, Peterborough's festival was the largest in recent years, while Port Perry's festival will return to Palmer Park on Saturday. In Vancouver, the 2024 edition will feature information for attendees. The Dragon Boat Festival holds cultural significance and provides a taste of home and tradition for many. In Taiwan, a nighttime racing event has added a modern twist to the ancient tradition. The community spirit is evident at festivals, with Peterborough's event raising over $200,000. The Regina Dragon Boat Festival also drew thousands of people, showcasing the popularity of this cultural celebration across the province.
